Preconditions:
1. The input string `text` is not null.
2. The input string `text` is not empty.
3. The input string `text` consists of lowercase English letters only.

Postconditions:
1. The method returns an integer representing the maximum number of instances of the word "balloon" that can be formed using the characters in the input string `text`.
2. Each character in the input string `text` can be used at most once to form instances of the word "balloon".
3. If no instances of the word "balloon" can be formed using the characters in the input string `text`, the method returns 0.